<h3>Initial Performance Planning</h3>
<p>Drupal has huge potential for scalability due to its structure. As a result, Drupal can be installed under a multitude of configurations. Splitting the database and search from the main web application is a common setup. Using a virtualized environment, such as a VMware Server, is an excellent way to create environments as needed for any possible configuration due to the ease of creating and scaling new machines.</p>
<p>With this flexibility, we need to address some additional performance planning prior to the installation of the operating system. Specifically in 2 areas.</p>
